  "meta_description": "Bronze has excellent machinability and has a wide range of applications such as general utility bearings and automobile fittings. Learn more about bronze's properties and applications for CNC machining.",
  "requested_url": "https://www.xometry.com/capabilities/cnc-machining-service/cnc-bronze",
  "sections": [
    {
      "hash": "0abc85767a64c09ea32576991dd4d39ac8737cfa",
      "heading": "Bronze CNC Machining",
      "level": "h1",
      "text": "Capabilities Custom Online CNC Machining Services Bronze CNC Machining Bronze CNC Machining Get instant quotes on custom bronze CNC machined parts with our Online CNC Machining Service. Make quick turn prototypes and production parts in days with free standard shipping on all US orders. ISO 9001:2015, ISO 13485, IATF 16949:2016, and AS9100D certified. ITAR registered. Get Your Custom CNC Machined Bronze Parts Instant Quote"
    },
    {
      "hash": "15673529b8e2f6a0d52325c3847028c10751f37e",
      "heading": "Copper 932",
      "level": "h2",
      "text": "Copper 932 Copper 932 is also known as bearing bronze. This alloy has excellent anti-friction properties, making it ideal for bearings, bushings, wear strips, and other light-duty applications."
    },
    {
      "hash": "e4ab850001d4c6b2e0e25485bbc908ab5a392ccb",
      "heading": "Finishes and Post-Processing Options",
      "level": "h3",
      "text": "Finishes and Post-Processing Options Because quality bronze forms only a surface layer of oxidation, it does not corrode the way many other metals do. As such, it does not always have to be coated. Xometry offers a range of surface finishes that work well for bronze. These can include the standard as-milled surface, bead blasting, or chemical coatings to prevent oxidation. To learn more about what surface finish is best for your application, contact us here ."
    },
    {
      "hash": "18a62b8110ef8b0203887fed4c198bd14a9eb613",
      "heading": "Cost-saving Design Tips",
      "level": "h3",
      "text": "Cost-saving Design Tips Bronze is a costly material and therefore its use must be optimized as much as possible. Design for manufacturing: Following design for manufacturing principles is one of the easiest ways to reduce costs in the machining process. Bronze is more forgiving of complex features due to its machinability, but there is a limit and this needs to be understood before manufacturing begins.Â A Xometry expert can provide insight into what can be achieved with machining bronze. Tolerancing: Bronze is easy to machine. Do not negate the production savings by over-tolerancing the part. This adds significant extra cost to the machining."
    },
    {
      "hash": "f4a02d7027ac0fabd1c606d4157615c43cc0b586",
      "heading": "Need CNC Machined Parts in Bronze?",
      "level": "h3",
      "text": "Need CNC Machined Parts in Bronze? Get Your Instant Quote"
    }
  ],
